The money-saving expert called on the current Prime Minister and future hopefuls to act after Cornwall Insights estimates bills rise 75 percent in October. He accused the Government of being "flaccid" in their approach. In a tweet, he said: "Just done an interview on @bbcr4today calling for Sunak, Truss and Johnson to urgently meet (they are part of same party after all) to come up with an action plan to urgently intervene in the disastrous predicted 77 percent energy price cap due Oct." FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...